 IGEN Networks Corp. and MachLink announce the mobile state of the art demonstration trailer. 
         










    










 






 











 









IGEN Networks Corp. and MachLink announce the mobile state of the art demonstration trailer.

May 26, 2011, 09:42 ET
		  		  					
						 from   iGen Networks Corp. 











 
















































 

 




















 



IGEN Networks Corp. (IGEN) is pleased to announce the mobile product demonstration trailer. 


VANCOUVER, May 26, 2011 /PRNewswire/ - IGEN in response to the unparalleled
 demand for communications and security within related country boarders
 and the oil industry IGEN has invested with MachLink in developing a
 comprehensive mobile demonstration unit that will showcase the advanced
 proprietary and patented technologies that meets and surpasses the
 demand for rural communications, government and industries need for the
 last mile data collection and security.


The unit will be a 20 foot mobile self contained demonstration trailer
 that will include two masts one with video surveillance equipment (
 thermal Cameras, Night Vision, PTZ camera, and standard vision camera)
 and the other with communication capability. It will also contain a
 weather station on the exterior and inside it will house our various
 intelligent or smart modules that will provide abilities for
 demonstration of our various smart video technologies, wall mounted
 monitors and a computer. The specific use for this unit will be for
 demonstration of our technologies through-out the US, and will include
 leak detection capabilities, trip wire detection, license recognition,
 border patrol technologies and general security monitoring
 capabilities.


IGEN's President, Monty Ormsby, says, "IGEN has strategically positioned
 the company to reach out to developed nations, especially in urban
 areas (The Last Mile), who historically once enjoyed significant
 communications and related business advantages. The company has
 established relationships in several countries of the Caribbean along
 with identified markets in Canada, US and Central America. IGEN
 understands that international business will be attracted to rural
 remote locations who utilize IGEN/MachLink patented and proprietary
 communication technologies that will provide state of the art
 connectivity to the rest of the world with reasonably priced
 connectivity. Rural areas and developing nations in partnership with
 IGEN/MachLink will have an economic advantage, as a place to do
 business. Two main reasons for this are minimal stranded costs and
 lower capital cost to provide world class connectivity and data
 transmission that will operate in all rural areas. This combined
 business opportunity positions IGEN/MachLink as the company of choice
 for our global clients"


About MachLink:


MachLink Corporation is a successful focused company dedicated to
 providing customers with leading edge communication and data services.
 MachLink offers patented broadband technology including high speed
 broadband wireless internet, digital phone service, wireless telephone
 service, multi-channel digital TV, FM radio and the latest addition to
 the technology suite includes a smart video solution.


On behalf of the Board of Directors IGEN Networks Corp. "Robert Nealon"
 Chairman of the Board Safe Harbor Statement under the United States Private Securities
 Litigation Act of 1995; This release may contain forward-looking
 statements that are affected by known and unknown risk, uncertainties
 and other factors which may cause the actual results, performance or
 achievements of the Company, or industry results, to be materially
 different from any future results, performance or achievements
 expressed, implied or anticipated by such forward-looking statement.
 The Company does not intend to update this information and disclaims
 any legal liability to the contrary.


On behalf of the Board of Directors:


IGEN Networks Corp. (IGEN: OTCBB) 
Mr. Robert Nealon  Chairman of the Board

   IGEN Networks Corp.  http://igen-networks.com   MachLink Corp.  www.machlink.ca 
